<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-03-11T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-03-11T22:00:00-05:00" n="778" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d778">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">834.01/26: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos
                                        Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-11T23:00:00-04:00">March 11, 1936—11
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received March 12—12:33 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>60. From Braden. Department’s 30, March 11, 6 p.m. Argentine Minister
                            Asunción has informed Saavedra Lamas that Stefanich agrees to procedure
                            outlined in my 57, March 10, 11 p.m. Therefore, he should have no
                            objection to procedure of identic notes.</p>
                        <p>Will confer with Saavedra Lamas and other delegates tomorrow noon.
                            [Braden.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Weddell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>